openmediavault-snapraid-aio (8.2) stable; urgency=low

  * Fix per-array state file collision: SYNC_WARN_FILE and SCRUB_COUNT_FILE
    are now written to /var/lib/snapraidaio/<uuid>.warnCount and
    /var/lib/snapraidaio/<uuid>.scrubCount instead of /usr/sbin/, so
    sync-warn and scrub-delay counters are isolated per array
  * Fix TMP_OUTPUT collision on concurrent runs: now /tmp/snapRAID-<uuid>.out
    instead of the shared /tmp/snapRAID.out
  * Create /var/lib/snapraidaio/ on install via postinst
  * Remove per-array state files when a config is deleted
  * Remove /var/lib/snapraidaio/ on package purge
  * Clarify in UI hints that hook_notification, before_hook_cmd, and
    after_hook_cmd run as root; note that snapraid_log_dir expects an
    absolute path
  * Fix add_del_threshold maximum: corrected from 10 to 1.0 in RPC schema
    and datamodel; update UI hint to show valid range 0.0–1.0
  * Fix healthchecks_id UI hint: clarify that only the UUID should be
    entered, not the full ping URL
  * Fix snapraid_conf: mark as required in the UI form and enforce
    minLength: 1 in the RPC schema so an empty array selection is rejected
  * Fix postinst: remove || : so Salt deployment failures surface as
    package install errors instead of being silently ignored
  * Fix getContainers: restrict to OMV_ROLE_ADMINISTRATOR; previously
    any authenticated user could enumerate Docker container names and images

 -- OpenMediaVault Plugin Developers <plugins@omv-extras.org>  Thu, 03 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000

openmediavault-snapraid-aio (8.1) stable; urgency=low
  * Replace global enable toggle with per-config Schedule button on the
    datatable; each config gets its own cron entry via OMV's Cron RPC;
    cron_uuid stored per-config so the schedule round-trips correctly
  * Remove Settings page, Settings navigation entry, and global enable field
  * Add Tools submenu to configs datatable: Force Sync (runs AIO script with
    --force-sync, bypasses delete/update thresholds, requires confirmation) and
    Sync (runs snapraid sync directly on the array); both stream output live
    via taskDialog
  * Add Run Now action to Tools submenu: runs the full AIO script for the
    selected config (equivalent to the cron job), output streamed via taskDialog
  * Add Last Log action to Tools submenu: displays the most recent
    SnapRAID-*.txt log file in the configured log dir (falls back to /root)
  * Add email_notifications toggle: enable/disable native OMV email per config;
    sender and receiver are pulled read-only from OMV system notification
    settings and hidden in the form when the feature is off
  * Add confirmation prompt on Schedule button warning that the array must
    be synced at least once before scheduling the AIO script
  * Change default schedule to midnight daily so users can adjust the time
    immediately without switching execution type
  * Improve SnapRAID array selector: show array name (label) instead of raw
    config file path; resolve symlinks to stable UUID-based paths as stored
    value; hide the /etc/snapraid.conf legacy symlink
  * Add Array name column to config list table
  * Add Scheduled column to config list table
  * Switch Apprise URL field to tagInput: supports multiple URLs as chips,
    empty value now correctly renders APPRISE_URL=() instead of APPRISE_URL=("")
  * Disable Telegram and Discord integrations (superseded by Apprise)
  * Pre-fill schedule comment with "SnapRAID AIO <array name>" on first-time creation
  * Split UI threshold section into Sync thresholds, Scrub settings,
    and SnapRAID options sections
  * Add descriptive hints to fields that previously had none
  * Fix misleading labels: force_zero, spindown, snap_status_notify,
    apprise, apprise_email, execute_before_spindown, smart_log_notify
  * Add info hint at top of config form linking to the AIO Script project page
  * Add hint below SnapRAID array selector to guide users who see an empty
    list to install the OMV SnapRAID plugin first
  * Add hint on spindown option that hd-idle is not installed automatically
  * Clarify in the UI that Apprise is auto-installed via pipx on first use
    and requires an internet connection at that point
  * Rename "Healthchecks" section title to "Healthchecks.io"
  * Hardcode CHECK_UPDATES=0; updates ship with the package
  * Fix APPRISE_URL rendered as Bash array in generated config file
  * Fix custom hook fields: disable before/after hook inputs and
    execute_before_spindown when custom_hook toggle is off
  * Fix SNAPRAID_CONF template: use empty string default instead of
    /etc/snapraid.conf so a missing array selection fails clearly at
    script runtime rather than silently running against the wrong array
  * Fix breadcrumb label: add parent route for /services/snapraidaio with
    title "SnapRAID AIO" so the breadcrumb shows "SnapRAID AIO" instead of
    the raw URL segment "Snapraidaio"
  * Fix executeCommand: guard empty snapraid_conf in sync case with a clear
    error message instead of passing -c "" to the snapraid binary
  * Fix executeCommand: check AIO config file exists before invoking
    run/force-sync and surface a clear "apply settings first" error
  * Fix deleteConfig: remove /etc/snapraid-aio-<uuid>.conf and linked cron entry
  * Fix Salt deploy exit code 1 when all AIO configs are deleted (add noop state)
  * Fix enumerateConfigFiles: wrap buildLabelMap() in try/catch so a missing
    /etc/snapraid directory returns an empty list instead of an RPC error dialog
  * Delete /etc/snapraid-aio-*.conf files on package purge

